    "This problem is compounded in tasks that are based on small datasets or specific applications where a lack of data limits the model's ability to generalize effectively.",
    "One critical approach to mitigating overfitting is to incorporate regularization techniques, such as dropout, L2 regularization, and batch normalization, as shown in electricity theft detection frameworks (Shi et al., 2023).",
    "These techniques have proven effective by reducing model complexity and enhancing generalization, particularly in imbalanced datasets where Transformers tend to amplify noise.",
    "Furthermore, grid search optimization for hyperparameters can balance model performance, as demonstrated in various applications within NLP and time series analysis (Shen et al., 2023; Eldele et al., 2024).",
    "In the context of time series forecasting, Transformer models face challenges with non-stationary data, which often leads to model degradation due to overfitting."
